## 5. Technical Implementation

### 5.1 Architecture Overview

```
Frontend (Next.js)
├── /beasiswa — Landing page
├── /register — Registration
├── /onboarding — Profile setup
└── /payment/beasiswa — Midtrans checkout

Backend (FastAPI)
├── /api/v1/auth/register — Fallback registration
├── /api/v1/auth/login — JWT auth
├── /api/v1/onboarding/profile — Profile CRUD
├── /api/v1/onboarding/postpay-complete — Post-payment setup
├── /api/v1/cohorts/{slug}/initiate — Payment initiation
├── /api/v1/cohorts/{slug}/confirm — Midtrans webhook
└── /api/v1/cohorts/public-config — Midtrans client key

Infrastructure
├── PostgreSQL (user data, enrollments, payments)
├── Midtrans (payment processing)
├── Supabase (optional OAuth, email verification)
└── Email Service (SendGrid/Postmark via admin dashboard)
```

### 5.2 Database Schema Changes

> ✅ All migrations consolidated into `backend/services/funnel_migrations.py` — runs at startup, idempotent on both SQLite and PostgreSQL.

**User Model Extensions (implemented in `sql_models.py`):**
```sql
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN name VARCHAR;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN onboarding_completed BOOLEAN DEFAULT 0;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN onboarding_prepay_completed BOOLEAN DEFAULT 0;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN onboarding_postpay_completed BOOLEAN DEFAULT 0;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN registration_status VARCHAR DEFAULT 'registered';
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN funnel_status VARCHAR DEFAULT 'registered';
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN onboarding_phase VARCHAR DEFAULT 'none';
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN bio TEXT;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN linkedin_url VARCHAR;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN github_url VARCHAR;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN learning_goals JSON;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN career_pathway_id VARCHAR;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN institution_id INTEGER;
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN instructor_type VARCHAR;
```

**Enrollment Model Extensions:**
```sql
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN cohort_id INTEGER;
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN payment_status VARCHAR;
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN payment_reference VARCHAR;
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN amount_usd FLOAT;
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN payment_attempt_status VARCHAR DEFAULT 'initiated';
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN payment_expires_at DATETIME;
ALTER TABLE enrollments ADD COLUMN payment_confirmed_at DATETIME;
```

**New Tables (created via `Base.metadata.create_all`):**
- `beta_cohorts` — slug, name, seat_cap, seats_sold, pricing_tiers (JSON), fixed_course_ids, is_active
- `payment_events` — order_id, cohort_slug, user_id, event_type, provider, payload
- `email_delivery_logs` — template_key, to_email, status, attempts, error_message
- `capstone_submissions` — full beta capstone with AI pre-grade + instructor review fields
- `alumni_profiles` — post-graduation public profile

### 5.3 Security & Production Readiness

**Critical Fixes Implemented (2026-04-24):**

| Fix | Description | Status |
|-----|-------------|--------|
| JWT Auth | Replaced predictable `devtoken` with signed JWT (HS256, 24h expiry) | ✅ Complete |
| Rate Limiting | 30/min for auth, 10/min for payment, 60/min for health | ✅ Complete |
| Payment Race Condition | Added `with_for_update()` row locking on enrollment check | ✅ Complete |
| DB Connection Pool | Configured pool_size=20, max_overflow=30 (50 total) | ✅ Complete |
| SQLite Guard | Aborts if SQLite detected in production (ENV=production) | ✅ Complete |

**Security Checklist:**
- [ ] JWT_SECRET_KEY set in production
- [ ] DATABASE_URL set to PostgreSQL (not SQLite)
- [x] Midtrans keys stored in encrypted admin secrets (via `_read_admin_secret` in `routers/cohorts.py`)
- [x] Rate limiting active on all public endpoints (SlowAPI: 30/min auth, 10/min payment)
- [ ] Email provider configured (SendGrid/Postmark) — set `EMAIL_PROVIDER` + `SMTP_*` env vars
- [ ] HTTPS enforced on production domain (Caddy handles — verify cert auto-renewal)

