## 6. Operational Requirements

### 6.1 Admin Dashboard Features

**Cohort Management:**
- Create/edit beta cohorts
- View seat sales in real-time
- Manually adjust seat count (for reconciliation)
- Toggle cohort active/inactive

**Payment Reconciliation:**
- View all payment events
- Manual webhook retry for stuck payments
- Refund processing (via Midtrans dashboard)

**Email Management:**
- Configure SMTP provider (SendGrid/Postmark)
- Test email delivery
- View email delivery logs
- Resend failed lifecycle emails

**Midtrans Configuration:**
- Set merchant ID, client key, server key
- Toggle sandbox/production environment
- View transaction status

### 6.2 Monitoring & Alerting

**Metrics to Track:**
- Registration rate (per hour)
- Payment initiation rate
- Payment success rate
- Webhook failure count
- Email delivery success rate
- Onboarding completion rate
- Support ticket volume

**Alert Thresholds:**
- Webhook failures > 5 in 1 hour → Alert
- Payment success rate < 90% → Alert
- Email delivery failure > 10% → Alert
- DB connection pool exhaustion → Alert

### 6.3 Support Workflow

**Common Issues & Resolution:**

| Issue | Symptoms | Resolution |
|-------|----------|------------|
| Payment stuck in pending | User paid but no enrollment | Manual webhook trigger from admin dashboard |
| Email not received | User reports no confirmation | Check email logs, resend from admin |
| Registration fails | Supabase not configured | Fallback to backend registration |
| Course access denied | Paid but can't access | Check enrollment status, manual activation if needed |

**Support Channels:**
- Email: support@vokasi.id
- WhatsApp: (optional, post-beta)
- FAQ page on landing site

