## 9. Success Criteria

### 9.1 Must-Have (Blockers if not met)
- [ ] 1,000 enrollments achieved
- [ ] Payment success rate > 90%
- [ ] No critical security incidents
- [ ] Support ticket volume < 50 total

### 9.2 Should-Have (Success indicators)
- [ ] Onboarding completion rate > 70%
- [ ] Course engagement > 50% of enrolled users
- [ ] NPS score > 40
- [ ] Referral rate > 10%

### 9.3 Nice-to-Have (Stretch goals)
- [ ] Viral social media moment
- [ ] Institution partnership signed
- [ ] Upsell to paid tier (future pricing)
- [ ] User-generated content (testimonials, reviews)

---

## 10. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|------------|--------|------------|
| Midtrans downtime | Low | High | Fallback messaging, manual payment processing |
| Payment fraud | Medium | Medium | Rate limiting, IP monitoring, manual review |
| Email deliverability issues | Medium | High | Multiple providers (SendGrid + Postmark fallback), DKIM/SPF setup |
| Supabase OAuth issues | Medium | Medium | Backend fallback registration clearly documented |
| Server overload at launch | Low | High | Connection pool configured, auto-scaling enabled |
| Low conversion rate | High | High | A/B test landing copy, adjust pricing tiers |

---

## 11. Post-Campaign Analysis

